Tina Turner not withstanding, love is not an emotion, and that&rsquo;s a good thing.
In today&rsquo;s Gospel (from the modern lectionary), Jesus tells his disciples to &ldquo;love your enemies&rdquo; and &ldquo;pray for those who persecute you.&rdquo;
But how? I find it difficult even to be around certain people, much less love them. Surely, Jesus wasn&rsquo;t serious when He told us to love our enemies, right? If Jesus meant what He said, then I must not know what love means.

Happiness Did you know that the word &ldquo;happiness&rdquo; means &ldquo;blessed?&rdquo;
Neither did I. But when I heard this on EWTN Radio the other day, I remembered there are two translations of the Beatitudes. One version goes with &ldquo;Blessed are . . .&rdquo; and the other with &ldquo;Happy are . . . .&rdquo; So, I guess it&rsquo;s true. The words are interchangeable.
Happiness, then, doesn&rsquo;t mean walking around in some lithium-induced state of bliss.
